
****HTML IS CASE INSENSITIVE****

1) What is HTML ?
->HTML stands for Hypertext markup language.HTML is not a programming language. It's a markup language. In fact, that is the technology's name: HyperText Markup Language.
It is a standerd text formatting language which is used to create and display pages on the web.

2)what is attribute in HTML?
->attributes are specified directly after the name of tag.inside the two angled brackets.
example <a href = "piyush.html"> here htef is attribute name , = is delimeter, piyush.htm is value.

3)what is diff betwn block level and inline element ?
->Inline elements include Bold(<b>),italic(<i>),links(<a>),span(<span>) and and these stacks horizontally.
Block elements include paragraphs (<p>), headings(<h>),<section>,<img>,<input>  these take up all of the available width they stack vertically.

4)how to define comments  in HTML?
-><!-- comments  -->

5)what are HTML tag used to define in tabular form ?
-><table> = defines a table.
<tr> = defines a row in table.
<th> = defines a header cell in a table.
<td> = defines a table data cell element.
<caption> = defines caption of table.
<col> = used to define element to specify column properties in a table.
<tbody> = used to group the body content in a table.
<thead> = used to group the header content in a table.
<tfooter> = used to group the footer content in a table.


6)how to create hyperlink in html ?
-> html provides anchor tag to create a hyperlink that links one page to another page 
hyperlink will redirected to another page.
unvisited link =  displayed in blue color.
visited link =  displayed in purple color.
active link = displayed in red color.

Syntax <a href = "piyush.html" > Link to piyush page </a> 

7)name the list in html ?
->
ordered list 
<ol>
  <li>Coffee</li>
  <li>Tea</li>
  <li>Milk</li>
</ol>

1.Coffee
2.Tea
3..Milk

unordered list                  
<ul>
  <li>Coffee</li>
  <li>Tea</li>
  <li>Milk</li>
</ul>

.Coffee
.Tea
.Milk

