13)Explain layout of html ?

<html>//start of html 
    <head>  //The <head> HTML element contains machine-readable information (metadata) about the document, like its title, scripts, and style sheets.
      <title></title>
      </head>
    <body> ///y. The <body> element contains all the contents of an HTML document, such as headings, paragraphs, images, hyperlinks, tables, lists, etc. Note: There can only be one <body> element in an HTML
        <h1> </h1>
        <h2> </h2>
        <h3> </h3>
        <h4> </h4>
        <h5> </h5>
        <h6> </h6>
    </body>
</html>   ///not compusory to close html tag




14)what is marquee tag ?
